---
import SectionLabel from "./SectionLabel.astro";
---

<section class="reveal" id="about">
  <SectionLabel index="01" label="about" cmd="cat README.md" />
  <div class="win" style="--win-accent: var(--color-cyan)">
    <div class="win-body text-[0.95rem] leading-relaxed text-fg-dim space-y-3.5">
      <p>
        Hey, I'm <span class="text-magenta font-semibold">Hunter</span>, an
        indie developer who likes shipping <span class="text-cyan">browser games</span>,
        <span class="text-cyan">real-time multiplayer apps</span>, <span class="text-cyan">Rust TUIs</span>,
        and <span class="text-cyan">native macOS utilities</span>. If it can run in a browser,
        a terminal, or a menu bar, I've probably built one.
      </p>
      <p>
        I daily-drive macOS with <a href="https://github.com/koekeishiya/yabai" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-blue underline decoration-blue/30 underline-offset-2">yabai</a>
        + <a href="https://sw.kovidgoyal.net/kitty/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-magenta underline decoration-magenta/30 underline-offset-2">kitty</a>
        themed in <span class="text-magenta">Tokyo Night</span>, and this site
        wears the same colors so it feels like a window I always have open.
      </p>
      <p>
        Currently obsessing over real-time multiplayer, beautiful system tools,
        and procedurally generated music for tiny browser games. Everything is
        open source.
      </p>
      <p class="font-mono text-xs text-comment pt-1 border-t border-border/60">
        <span class="text-green">$</span> philosophy: if it's worth building,
        it's worth over-engineering at 2 AM.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
